Reference:
    Daubert, T. E., & Danner, R. P. (1985).
    Data compilation tables of properties of pure compounds.

Notes:
    This file contains coefficients for NSRDS functions of temperature for the
    properties of various incompressible liquids. More properties are provided
    by the reference. This is a subset containing only the properties that we
    typically require.

    Note that the NSRDS functions used for specific heat have been modified
    from the reference to be per unit mass, rather than per mole. Note also
    that standard entropy is not defined by the reference, and is set to zero
    in the data below.

    These functions can be used directly as Function1-s. Or, they can be used
    as part of a thermodynamic model. In the latter case, the thermodynamic
    model will need to be selected in constant/physicalProperties as follows:

        thermoType
        {
            type            heRhoThermo;
            mixture         pureMixture;
            transport       NSRDS;
            thermo          NSRDS; // or NSRDS14
            equationOfState NSRDS;
            specie          specie;
            energy          sensibleEnthalpy; // or sensibleInternalEnergy
        }

    These properties can then be used directly; e.g., for water:

        mixture
        {
            ${${FOAM_ETC}/thermoData/NSRDSphysicalProperties!H2O}
        }

\*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
FoamFile
{
    format      ascii;
    class       dictionary;
    location    "constant";
    object      NSRDSphysicalProperties;
}
